The Riesz-Markov-Kakutani theorem (ComplexRMK in Lean) states that for a continuous linear functional `L` on `C₀(X, C)`, there exists a complex measure `μ` such that `∫_X g dμ = L(g)` for all `g ∈ C₀(X, C)`. 

